The paper deals with probabilistic Büchi automata, which are a type of automata on infinite strings. The results presented in the paper are related to decidability and complexity of problems, characterization of languages, and introduction of a new type of automata. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the most likely ones are:

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with formal verification, which is a topic closely related to logic in computer science. The results on decidability and complexity of problems are also typical of this sub-category.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper deals with automata on infinite strings, which is a topic within formal languages and automata theory. The results on characterization of languages and introduction of a new type of automata are also typical of this sub-category.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with computational models and their properties, which is a topic within data structures and algorithms. The results on complexity of problems are also typical of this sub-category.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper deals with formal models of computation, which is a topic within programming languages. The results on characterization of languages and introduction of a new type of automata are also typical of this sub-category.
- cs.LT (Learning Theory): The paper deals with probabilistic models
